This means you can now send messages to your validator with exactly the same communication that validators/miners use.

It also completely simplifies all frontend api access applications because of how easily you can send messages to the subnet. It makes it even easier for validators to setup frontends for the subnet.

Here is a code sample of the new api that all validators will host.

```python
import bittensor as bt
from cortext.protocol import StreamPrompting
meta = bt.metagraph( netuid=18 )
wallet = bt.wallet( wallet="ck", name="hk" )
uid = your validator uid

  provider = "Claude",
  model = "claude-3-opus-20240229"
  uid = 1
)
answer = bt.dendrite( wallet=wallet )( meta.axons[uid], synapse, 60)
print(answer)
```
